/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/server/sprites/enemies/dimension-707 (all enemy categories extracted with 16 sprites per category: fodder, standard, elite, and boss).\n>\n> **Maps:** 25 maps, coverage OK — All three steps succeeded. STEP 1 generated 25 maps (24 unique encounter maps + 1 reference image reused for dense-wilderness) in 129.9s with collision masks. STEP 2 confirmed full coverage: \"v2 map coverage OK for dimension 707: all 14 encounter types have maps.\" STEP 3 uploaded all 25 map PNGs to s3://schoolland-tbg-maps/sprites/maps/dimension-707/\n>\n> **Overworld:** Dimension 707 (Escapement): registered 0 structures (v2 decorations-only)\n>   backgroundPath:      sprites/map-objects/dimension-707/background.png\n>   hexDecorationsPath:  sprites/map-decorations/dimension-707\n>\n> **Enemy agent:** Every encounter profile sits at or slightly above the dim-0 baseline (boss 25% vs 8%, calamity 8% vs 0%, wilderness identical, dumb rates matching). Balance is locked.\n>\n> FINAL BALANCE (dim-0 baseline: expert 54.2 / dumb 13.4 / gap 40.8):\n> Dimension 707 \"Escapement\" — expert 57.9 / dumb 14.8 / gap 43.1. All 16 enemies have skill gap >= 25.9, no dumb solo rate above dim-0's max of 33.3, all bosses at 0% dumb solo and 66.7% expert party (exactly the dim-0 boss band).\n>\n> ROSTER (16 enemies, dimension 707):\n> - FODDER: tin-soldier (1, rush swarm, bayonet ranks), clockwork-hound (2, move-165 pack closer), oiler (2, kite, slowing oil jet + drainBlue slick zone), sweeper (2, kb-70 broom shove + wall slams)\n> - STANDARD: cultist-hook (3, onHit pull-60 formation dragger), spring-snake (3, 130-length lungeThrough pack lunger), cultist-torch (4, kite, AoE flask + suppressed + lit-slick damage zone), cog-thrower (4, kite artillery, red-2 cadence circle at range 190)\n> - ELITE: brass-golem (6, hp-185 move-70 tank, 38-dmg haymaker + barrier), piston-ram (7, red-2 charge, kb-60 + lungeThrough + wallSlam), bell-knight (7, self-centered toll applying winded-2 = move/block lockout + barrier), winder-priest (6, suppressed key-bolt + heal/barrier zones)\n> - BOSS: cult-master (10, kite, winded key-turn + heal/drainRed zones, onDeath spawns 2 cultist-hooks), iron-foreman (12, threat, onDeath spawns 3 tin-soldiers), shepherd-engine (12, hp-360, 110-radius half-circle raking sweep), clock-spider (13, mobile threat, 40-dmg slowing skewer + tick-mine zones)\n>\n> WHAT I TUNED AND WHY (5 test iterations, 1272 games each):\n> 1. Purged the stale prior 707 roster from the DB (would have polluted encounter scenarios).\n> 2. Discovered scripted AI only ever uses the FIRST attack ability — every enemy's signature/role-defining attack is deliberately slotted first; zones/barriers are secondary depth.\n> 3. Iter 2: buffed oiler/sweeper/bell-knight/winder-priest (all near-free wins; bell-knight was energy-starved to 3 attacks/game — made its toll red-1); gutted cog-thrower's cross-map alpha strike (6 copies dealt 144 dmg at 272 reach before the hero acted — skill-independent); shortened spring-snake reach (155+140 move made spacing useless, inverting skill); softened iron-foreman for parties (33% party-expert), hardened clock-spider (67% expert is no boss), traded shepherd-engine knockback for hp (solo-hard/party-free).\n> 4. Iter 3-4: fixed piston-ram/spring-snake's structural gap problem — at their costs, budget-6 bought one free duel while budget-18/25 bought an unwinnable pack even for experts; raised ram to cost 7 (fewer copies) which took its gap from 18.5 to 40.8.\n> 5. Iter 5-6: reshaped spring-snake into a cost-3 glass pack-lunger (hp 75, dmg 18, pairs at budget 6) — gap went 22 → 44.5, dumb 26 → 18.5. Its \"snapped mainspring\" description fits the pack framing unchanged; no other enemy's look diverged from spec.\n>\n> Report: /home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/balance-report-dim-707.json; final templates in DB (dimension 707) and /tmp/dim707/*.json.\n>\n> **Item agent:** Iteration 3 is clean — no flags, no worse-than-baseline items, rarity tracks (baseline 105; commons 114-139; uncommons 131-155; rares 152-169).\n>\n> FINAL WEAPONS (16, dimension 707 \"Escapement\"):\n>\n> Swords\n> - d707-tin-sword (common, 114) — deliberately the floor item; cheap bendy blade, still comfortably above baseline\n> - d707-brass-saber (common, 127) — mobile cutter with a lungeThrough draw cut; buffed heavy 29→32 after starting bottom-of-commons\n> - d707-sawblade (uncommon, 133) — ragged rip + slowing tearing drag; buffed across the board (34/18/16 → 38/22/20) after launching below common crossbow\n> - d707-clock-hand (rare, 157) — long thin reach sword (r104 sweep, 135px lunging Hour Strike); untouched from v1\n>\n> Spears\n> - d707-iron-pike (common, 131) — pure reach (160px thrust); untouched\n> - d707-piston-spear (uncommon, 155) — big-knockback wallSlam drive + recoil-hop disengage; nerfed twice (drive 32→30→28, kb 55→45, hop kb 40→35) because ranged-style safety made it crowd the rare band at 96% WR\n> - d707-drag-hook (rare, 155) — halberd-pattern rare with a 1-red Yank (pull 70); untouched\n>\n> Bows\n> - d707-crossbow (common, 139) — top common; simple 270px bolt kit\n> - d707-ratchet-bow (uncommon, 143) — heavier draw + 1-turn rooting Pinning Shot\n> - d707-coil-bow (rare, 169) — top item; nerfed hard from 190/100%WR (mainspring 28→23 dmg, 330→305 range; stagger shot kb 60→30) — the cheap 60-kb kiting shove was the main offender\n>\n> Staffs\n> - d707-brass-staff (common, 127) — bolt + point-blank repulse\n> - d707-chime-staff (uncommon, 145) — AoE Discordant Toll nerfed (suppressed 2→1 turns, 15→13 dmg) after outscoring two rares\n> - d707-winding-key (rare, 159) — crozier-pattern tension release (big ranged AoE + knockback spring coil); untouched\n>\n> Two-handed (these pay a shield tax in the test, so they run hotter stats)\n> - d707-great-wrench (common, 124) — wallSlam crusher; untouched\n> - d707-gear-axe (uncommon, 131) — buffed 43/38/20 → 48/44/24 after landing below common bows\n> - d707-pendulum-maul (rare, 152) — buffed damage (46/42/20 → 52/48/24) then fixed the last rarity inversion mechanically: reach r95→102 / 130→140px and counterweight shove kb 45→55 for safety, not more raw damage\n>\n> Also cleaned up: deleted 12 stale d707- items in the DB from an earlier generation attempt (minute-hand, wire-bow, pry-bar, etc.) that weren't in the spec and weren't referenced by any player inventory.\n>\n> Key balance insight: ranged/reach safety dominates this sim, so melee weapons need noticeably higher damage or reach/knockback tools to score at parity — that drove every fix.\n>\n> Report: /home/ben/Projects/turn-based-game/item-report-dim-707.json (3 seeds, 459 games, zero flags). Item JSONs kept at /tmp/d707-items/.\n\nTwo things worth your attention beyond the verbatim result. First, the balance agent and the QA verdict disagree in tone: the agent says \"balance is locked,\" but the independent QA re-run flagged 11 enemies — mostly `dumb-win-high` (a bot with no tactics still wins 18–33% of the time) plus three bosses at `expert-win-low`. The agent's own notes argue these sit inside the dim-0 baseline band, so the flags may be threshold artifacts rather than real problems, but `warn` is what the gate returned and nothing reconciled the two.\n\nSecond, both the enemy and item agents reported deleting stale dimension-707 rows from a prior attempt — consistent with the untracked 707 files that were already in the working tree when I started. Those on-disk artifacts have now been overwritten by this run. Everything is still untracked, so nothing is committed yet.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"566c71d6-9b48-4033-a4db-c9bb0f034664","total_cost_usd":13.909093500000003,"usage":{"input_tokens":8950,"cache_creation_input_tokens":37346,"cache_read_input_tokens":144872,"output_tokens":8362,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":37346,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":